reviews.text: This is a great place to pick berries! We picked blueberries here on wild blueberry weekend and there was ample space to pick and enjoy the day. Beautiful property and great, pleasant and personable people that own and operate the place. We will be back for more!

Check their Facebook page for updates about when they‚Äôre open for picking and what you can currently pick. We went and had a wonderful time. The man who owns the place was very friendly and taught us about the different varieties of blueberries they had. Was definitely a fun time!

WoW!!! Best strawberries I've ever had!!üçì Convenient and decent prices.  A little sketchy pulling out of the driveway because people drive way too fast thru this area even though it's well posted - pickers ahead üëçüçì

A great place for berry picking with a small, hardworking team running the show. Love the berries, the old school honor system for already-picked boxes and pumpkins out front. Looking forward to many more summers picking with my family.

We‚Äôve been loyal supporters of this small farm for years. Today my family and I decided to take our friends with their children blueberry picking. We accidentally ended up on a very poorly labeled area where we weren‚Äôt supposed to pick.
The employee drove up to us on a golf cart and started screaming at us, he yelled ‚ÄúI want you out of here, just get out!!! Get out of here! Get out!‚Äù

He didn‚Äôt simple tell us we shouldn‚Äôt pick there, he threw us out . Our children were so confused and frightened, my daughter started crying.
We apologized and explained that it‚Äôs an honest mistake, the sign wasn‚Äôt visible and we would never pick blueberries from a reserved area but he screamed at us to leave.
We have never been treated with this much hatred and aggression.

placeDetails.name: Chase Farms
placeDetails.formatted_address: 1488 N Berwick Rd, Wells, ME 04090, USA

reviews.text: Chase Farms in Wells, Maine is a historic, family-run farm known for fresh produce, local meats, baked goods, and apple picking. Seasonal highlights include pumpkins, cider, and maple syrup demos each spring and fall.

Great local farmstand. Fresh produce, tomatoes,  peppers,  corn and more. Delicious chicken pies, and variety of meats. Lots of tasty bakery and treats, including cider donuts and apple tarts! Pumpkins, mums and more. A must stop with great friendly staff!

They are way over priced but I pass by on my way to Dover NH so it is covenient. Stopped here for fresh Silver Queen corn and was extremely disappointed. At 99cents an ear it was definitely overpriced but we love silver queen so I bought 6 ears. Not one ear had a full cob of kernels and 2 ears were only 50 percent full. I will not stop here again.

Quaint place.
Farm fresh produce, homemade bakery and local produced beverages. Nice people there.
Price wise on the tad high side but it is to be expected at a local farm store.
Will be going back to see what they have for pumpkins.

Great local family run farm and stand
Lots of produce,  their own meat. Baked goods. Terrific place

Best vegetable stand ever & amazingly kind & helpful staff love this place. I have lived in this area for a very long time & I love this place never go anywhere but there for my Summer produce . Great place supporting my local farmers daughter waterboro location. Thank you for another year of delicious fresh vegetables.

I am definitely biased, but this is hands down the best farm stand in at least the surrounding three towns. The only other stands even comparable to this one are under the same ownership and management -- sweetest freaking corn you'll ever have in your life. They carry lean, fresh ground beef, and the produce assortment is constantly changing with the seasons. üëè The farmers that own this farm are some of the nicest, hardest working people you will ever meet.
Stopped in with my sister in law for corn.  We had a family outing.  Corn was delicious.

I love this family owned farm, and the vegetables are amazing. Best vegetables around. Amazing people. I love supporting our local own family oriented businesses.  Wish we could buy vegetables all year around. I look forward to them every summer. üåΩü•ïü•íü•îüçÖüçÜü´õüßÑü´öü´ëüçâüçàü´ê
Nice, fresh produce. The sweet corn is especially good. Reasonable prices. We drive from Sanford and it's always worth the trip.

Used to absolutely love their pies but lately they‚Äôve been awful!!    $28.00 for a blueberry pie that was worse than a grocery store week old pie..  do not expect what used to be‚Ä¶.   Youll be disappointed

Love this place so much!! Try to swing by as much as possible just to see what‚Äôs new! Honor system and cash only (or check). Quality plants, fresh cut flowers, pies / baked goods and other treats like cookies and zucchini bread. Must visit!
Hidden gem in Goose Rocks beach area of Kennebunkport. Fresh baked pies, cookies, and other baked treats. The blueberry pie is a standout!
Such yummy blueberry pie!! Highly recommend stopping by here and grabbing some fresh produce and baked goods!
Very cute farm store with a self-service checkout station. Off season they have pies, prepared dishes, sauces, jams, syrup, and some herb and tomato plant starters that look very health (May 2025)

Name: Frith Farm
Address: 61 Ash Swamp Rd, Scarborough, ME 04074, USA

placeDetails.name: Frith Farm
placeDetails.formatted_address: 61 Ash Swamp Rd, Scarborough, ME 04074, USA

reviews.text: Great place to get fresh organic vegetables!  The staff is friendly and accommodating offering up advice and details on their farming skills.  The farm stand is self-service with nice displays of freshly picked vegetables.  Worth a stop when in the area!
Self service farm stand and CSA. Beautiful location and offer reasonably price plants, including perennials and veg garden plants.
Amazing fresh veggies and really good rye bread. This is a CSA based business.
I love this farm.  We get our veggies here.  The no-till farming is impressive.  Plus there's kittens.

The home of my CSA. Spendy but you get what you get: choice of your vegetables, herbs and flowers to round out your meal and dinner table respectively. Beyond that, it's idyllic and the kittens running around are just part of the fun.

I drove by this cute farm, December 5th, and noticed their fabulous Christmas Trees.. I turned around at the next driveway. So glad I turned around. I found the most beautiful tree! When I went in to pay, they also included apple cider! I have to be honest and say I've lived in Maine for 52 years and have never had apple cider before. I was pleasantly surprised, it's so good! Thank you to the two ladies that were there.

Nice property. Limited varieties of apples (only 3) and pretty picked over. No more apple crisp left.
But we had a fun time on a beautiful Fall day.
So many apples for pick your own, with pumpkin patches as well. The store is so cute and I thought the prices were fair. We will definitely be back!!
Delicious cider, fabulous apples & pumpkins, great service from down to earth wonderful people, and a huge selection of Maine products in the store.
This place this a sort of a country store. They have all kinds of goods inside as well as plants outside.
You can taste the love that goes into producing these farm fresh vegetables. Such a beautiful organic farm and amazing to see how it has grown over the years!
If you are looking for beautiful, delicious, nutrient rich organic food grown and sourced with integrity and love - look no further. Girard Farm is a haven and worth the visit!
The owners could not be nicer and they grow the most lush and delicious produce. I‚Äôll be back again and again. Can‚Äôt wait to visit the farm stand again in summer 2025!
Staff very friendly. Produce excellent!
What a find! Have been a customer all summer long and loving it! Josh is great and the veggies are wonderful!

placeDetails.formatted_address: 316 Fowler Rd, Cape Elizabeth, ME 04107, USA

Always good, fresh, organic vegetables & fruit. Love the self serve style stand too.
Great place for seedlings. Top quality. Friendly staff. Family owned.

placeDetails.name: Ives Berry Farm
placeDetails.formatted_address: 133 Flag Pond Rd, Saco, ME 04072, USA

reviews.text: Had the best time! Such a beautiful and tranquil blueberry orchard! So appreciate Wayne and his family‚Äôs hospitality. Loved the delicious berries! Enjoyed tasting such a wide variety‚Äî who knew! Great value for a beautiful delicious experience!
Impressive operation, super fun picking with my son today, look forward to next year's crop, thank you for your hard work!
Small wonderful pick-your-own blueberry farm. Like 7 different varieties. Nice
Beautiful tasty berries, many varieties, nice family farm!
In all ways, just lovely.

What a gem!   Enormous selection of the widest variety of pumpkins and gourds I've ever seen.  Mums were beautiful and  everything priced better than anyone around.    Step inside and you'll be greeted by the owner's friendly coworkers, his beautiful dogs!   We look forward to going back!

I‚Äôd give it zero if I could. Most of the Veggies were rotted with fruit flies everywhere. When I tried to check the produce in the bushel because of how awful other items were the man said ‚ÄúI don‚Äôt need to sell that to you, I can sell it to someone else.‚Äù I‚Äôm assuming bc I kept looking.  I explain I‚Äôm a disabled vet and my brain struggles to process  but he was rude anyway. I‚Äôll never return nor recommend this place to anyone! Went to Meservey about 5 miles away  (thanks to another reviewer) and the produce was AMAZINGLY fresh and the gentleman who came out to help was so super kind!

There was a FB Marketplace ad for 10 lbs of wild blueberries for $28. What a great deal right? We walked in and there were 4 people sitting at a table and they didn't even look up. We came to check out the blueberries so we opened up a box. They were stored in a carboard shoe box shaped box. We opened the first two boxes and they had mold growing on the top of the blueberries. We didn't buy them. Some ads are too good to be true. The other food items they sold were not good looking either. I noticed that someone said that this was a good place as an alternative to grocery stores. I disagree. If you buy here, you're buying stuff that in a couple days would go to the pigs. Support another local farm (there are plenty) that has good and fresh produce and the price is honest. After leaving here, I went to Meservey Farms and picked up a lb of FRESH green beans and a couple zucchini for $3.50. Other farms I would recommend are Snell and Frugal Farmers.

I wish I took pictures of the blueberries to post but I thought that would be rude when I was there. Honestly I should have because the people there wouldn't have noticed.
Down to earth market.  Not fancy. But nice fresh produce and good prices. Great place to supplement grocery budget with fruit and vegetables.
Great plants. Awesome prices.  Fantastic Produce.  Year after year after year.

Name: Lavigne Strawberry Farm
Address: 158 Whichers Mill Rd, Sanford, ME 04073, USA

placeDetails.name: Lavigne Strawberry Farm
placeDetails.formatted_address: 158 Whichers Mill Rd, Sanford, ME 04073, USA

reviews.text: What a charming place! I went early in the morning on a weekday and had the place almost to myself. The staff was very personable and the prices were super reasonable.

Best place in southern ME to pick strawberries üçì
Love the friendly staff!
Had alot of fun picking with the grands, i  thinks i ate as much as i picked, lol always fun memories, just need some coolwhip later and yummy!!!!
We look forward to coming every year!
Great place!! We took our daughter today for her 1st Birthday! She had so much fun picking and tasting! Big red stained smiles! Very clean and well maintained fields! Thank you!

Name: Leary Farm

placeDetails.name: Leary Farm
placeDetails.formatted_address: 269 Flag Pond Rd, 1006 Portland Rd, Saco, ME 04072, USA

reviews.text: Had a great time at Leary Farm. Went pumpkin picking and it was the perfect fall outing. The farm is beautiful, well-organized, and had a great selection of pumpkins in all shapes and sizes. The atmosphere was friendly and family-oriented, with a classic New England charm. Staff was helpful and welcoming, and everything felt clean and well cared for. Whether you‚Äôre with kids, friends, or just looking for that perfect pumpkin, Leary Farm is a must-visit. Highly recommend for a fun, seasonal experience!

I went for the first time last week and love it. Everything is so fresh, especially green beans. Really enjoyed my cooked green beans and went to get a whole bunch more today. I wish I knew this place sooner. It's a pretty reasonable price as well. Service is awesome. The lady will answer any questions you may have. I showed some of the pictures to my coworker, and they are already planning to swing by.

After arriving at the correct place (as Google Maps will take you to their Leary Farm house), they had a minimal selection of pumpkins. They did have a good variety of pumpkins. A small shop with various specialty foods and trinkets. My 3 children and I purchased 3 LG jack-o'-lantern üéÉ 1 specialty pumpkin and 1 mini pumpkin and I paid $55 and some change. It's conveniently located right off Rt. 1 in Saco!
Beautiful assortment of Pumpkins, fruits and vegetables!!
Very nice selection of pumpkins & gourds for the fall season

reviews.text:
üçéüçèüçéüçèüçé Forgot five stars; this place gets five apples! üçè‚ú® What a fun place to go with family or friends. No kids needed to enjoy this place! üë®‚Äçüë©‚Äçüëß‚Äçüë¶ My husband and I drove up on a Saturday afternoon. We started with lunch at our favorite food truck, Meet on the Street, and some delicious adult ciders. üçª Because it‚Äôs fall, y‚Äôall‚Äîwhy not! üçÇüçÅ Next, this well-run operation had golf carts to drive you to the field. üöú We enjoyed apple üçè and blueberry picking. They were the best blueberries we‚Äôve ever hand-picked! ü´êüíô We will definitely return next year for some of their other fruit options. On the way out, we picked up a few cider donuts. üç© Enjoy them right away when they‚Äôre hot! They will melt in your mouth. üòã

**Travel note:** üì± You'll lose cell service, so plan your journey before you leave. Follow the travel tips on Libby's website. Your phone might lie to you! üó∫Ô∏èüöó

I've missed Blueberry season last few years returning home to visit family, so when I saw Libby's was still open, we had to go. We got 10 lbs blueberries and 2 bags apples for a little over $100. But it was worth it because you can't find the flavor anywhere else across the states. My BFF and I had an amazing time and experience to last a lifetime. Clean place, friendly staff, and beautiful scenery.

I‚Äôll preface this by saying we were three grown men who decided to go blueberry picking while visiting Maine (because you can‚Äôt do that in Missouri)‚Ä¶.and we had a great time.  It was beautiful being out into he blueberry and raspberry fields.  The staff was super nice.  There was live music (but the beer truck wasn‚Äôt open). The fresh smoothies were delicious‚Ä¶as were the berries!   Well worth the drive from Portland.

Best apple picking experience we‚Äôve ever had. Food trucks were awesome. Donuts and cider was even better. We loved the live music and the chauffeured golf cart rides to the orchard. This place has got it figured out!

Beautiful farm and beautiful fruit. The only downfall I would say would be how everything is priced because it would be difficult for a big family to come and enjoy themselves because pricing is based on how many people are in your group. Other then the way it's priced I would have given a 5 star because it is a nice orchard.

Name: Orchard Ridge Farm
Address: 236 Sebago Lake Rd, Gorham, ME 04038, USA

placeDetails.name: Orchard Ridge Farm
placeDetails.formatted_address: 236 Sebago Lake Rd, Gorham, ME 04038, USA

reviews.text: Went on a first date here. And it was amazing. Sadly, the apple picking was dwindling down. And the apples got some weather damage.  But we found a couple. The property is beautiful üòç.  Just a walk through the orchard was so peaceful. The shop had some yummy coffee drinks too! Service there is so friendly.

Popped into this super cute spot for the first time since the new owners took over, and I‚Äôm so glad I did! The menu is packed with options‚Äîwhether you're in the mood for a breakfast sandwich, a hot latte, fresh bagels, pizza, a burger, or even a salad. Plus, they‚Äôve got all sorts of fun pantry goodies, gifts, beer, wine, fresh eggs, and some chilled and frozen items.

While you wait for your food, you can wander outside to say hey to the chickens, goats, donkey, and pig!

We decided to hang out and had lunch at the big table that fits 4-6 people. We tried a little bit of everything: breakfast sandwich, pizza, burger, and falafel wrap. Everything was soooo tasty! There are also a couple of bar seats if you want to grab a quick bite. Can‚Äôt wait to come back!

Well....the orchard had only 2 varieties of apples. For $3 per pound, I expected a lot more. And, I was sad to see the animals' living conditions. The chickens were too crowded in their pen, the 2 goats didn't have any grazing area to speak of, and the one pig had no water in its small pen. There was a friendly rabbit hopping around.

The store was very nice, with lots of gourmet goodies and an impressive array of meats. The one staff person we saw was very friendly.  A nice display of pumpkins was outside.  But their website offered a much better experience!

Great big tasty blueberries and lots of them in a manicured idyllic setting. Friendly people, reasonable pricing, and a really wonderful bakery that had some of the best hot scones we have ever had. Easily recommended and 5 stars!

Really enjoyed staying here overnight in my camper and sampling some yummy meals and also enjoyed watching families enjoy immersing themselves in the experience of apple picking and friendly encounters with farm animals. Also, they are decorated for Halloween and have beautiful pumpkins and marigolds for sale. The apple trees were prolific but unfortunately the recent hurricane toppled some trees and lost many apples to the ground early.  The farm is lovely and right on the Sebago to sea greenway which I took advantage of with my dog. My dog is good with farm animals but still, I kept her up because of the food service & young families ( There is a playground and lawn games in the picnic area too). The staff work hard and are friendly and helpful. Market has an abundant variety of homegrown fresh foods and treats!
Great spot! Grabbed some pizza and apple cider for a late lunch. Can‚Äôt go wrong with any of the pizzas on the menu. And we will be back for the apple cider donuts.
Awesome little orchard. They have fresh cider and hard cider. Terrific afternoon with the family
Great experience and loved the variety of apples available

They have very very best apple cider donuts üç© & apple cider in Standish Maine , you can pick your own apples or buy them inside . you can buy maple syrup, honey , fruit, vegetables, jams, üåΩ, blueberry, strawberries, Christmas trees in winter time
If you are visiting Maine come here
Staff is always helpful and friendly, and they have great local produce at reasonable prices. I love Randall's!

Name: Saco River Farms
Address: 29 Weeman Rd, Steep Falls, ME 04085, USA

placeDetails.name: Saco River Farms
placeDetails.formatted_address: 29 Weeman Rd, Steep Falls, ME 04085, USA

reviews.text: The farmstead has a great selection of meat and goat dairy products. The farm is not open to the public, they really don't like it if you go to the animal area.  If you are looking to see goats don't come here, go to Sunflower Farm Creamery instead. However if you are looking for meat and dairy products this is better.

I wish I could give this place higher than a five star! Only place that I can find goat meat that is worth buying. Had a fantastic conversation with who I assume is the owner and he was just fantastic! I was going to try some pickled carrots from a brand I do not know and he convinced me with his rave reviews to try the other flavor. Let me tell you they were fantastic! He was super knowledgeable and super friendly. I just wish it was closer lol I can‚Äôt wait to go get more of the carrots.
Nice farm stand!  Goat meat and goat gelato, goat yogurt! Just what I was looking for. They also have duck, beef, and variety of pickled products.

Five stars! As much as I‚Äôd love to hide this farm for myself, I‚Äôm left salivating for more after consuming everything I bought three days ago.

It‚Äôs important to note that I am normally not a goat cheese fan. I am converted forever.

The store is small and packed with delicious charcuterie foods like meats, spreads, crackers and cheeses from Maine. The wine and beer selections are wonderful and handpicked by the owners. They make their own goat cheeses that are AHüëèüèºMAYüëèüèºZINGüëèüèº. The cheddars, valencay, and mizithra are the reason I will return regularly. Smooth, full-bodied flavors make these cheeses easy to pair and easy to just spoon feed yourself.

They also offer produce and frozen meats from great Maine farms. I highly recommend you give these wonderful people your business for gifts for loved ones and to up your cooking game. 11/10
Definitely worth the stop. Great selection of local produce, meat, food & drink ‚Äî lots of organic.

placeDetails.name: Shady Brook Farm
placeDetails.formatted_address: 10 W Loop Rd, Biddeford, ME 04005, USA

reviews.text: We've been getting our fresh produce from this farm for as long as I can remember. Prices are reasonable and staff is friendly and helpful. Can't go wrong here. Open daily during season 10-6.
Great selection, fresh, local,  friendly,  glad I stopped in! üôÇ
Wonderful vegetables, wonderful people, salt of the earth. We've been coming here for at least 20 years.
Great local vegetables and sweet corn! Support the local economy, small farmers and working landscapes.
Just a small local farm stand, been there for years, just like to help out local people
The farm and store are great. We brought my son apple picking here and he loves it. He had fun meeting the cows and goats, and hopping on the old tractor
Nothing like farm fresh eggs, meat and vegetables.   My wife and I shop here 2-3 times a week.  Never disappointed.   Wonderful family owned farm.
I got a Hiwaiian Pizza there yesterday. Best I've had. Great sauce and crust. Good size pieces of ham and pineapple!
Great strawberry and rhubarb picking today!
Jalape√±o‚Äôs were very good nice heat to them  the corn not so good seemed old half were rotten on top I could see in the middle of September, but not the middle of August

The best farm to jar jam on the planet!!! They know me as the "crazy guy from NJ"  who will drive up to buy their stuff at the weekly Farmers Market. Just don't buy their triple berry - save them all for me lol.
Super friendly and always a pleasure to deal with and they always go out of their way to accommodate.

It's not really spring until we stop at Uncle's to pick up seedlings to start our garden. We drive from Portland, passing other greenhouses because we love the service, the selection, and the prices!

We DID just learn they come up for the Portland Farmer's Market in Deering Oaks, so once we get a better idea of what space we have, we're gonna have to stop in and see them there!
Save gas. Visit this friendly local farm stand with veggies, flowers and honey.  We got all we needed.
I go here every year and they are fantastic.  Super friendly owners and plants that always produce.
Visit this local farm stand for your vegetables, flowers and honey.  Super nice with lots of options.
